<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-1248] PatternLayout Nano timestamp does not work</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1248</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As reported by jiri463 on &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/34683550/log4j-2-5-patternlayout-nano-timestamp-does-not-work&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;StackOverflow&lt;/a&gt;, specifying %nano in a pattern layout always renders zero values instead of the expected nanotime.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note for StackOverflow users: this ticket refers to the &lt;a href=&quot;http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/layouts.html#NanoTime&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;%nano&lt;/tt&gt; conversion pattern&lt;/a&gt; in pattern layout, which displays the result of &lt;tt&gt;System.nanotime()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This function is &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; related to the &lt;a href=&quot;http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/layouts.html#PatternClass&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;%date&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt; date pattern with microsecond or nanosecond precision that was introduced in Log4j 2.11.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12928836">LOG4J2-1248</key>
            <summary>PatternLayout Nano timestamp does not work</summary>
